html:
Ocean Sunset Forest Neon Candy Arctic
This example uses CSS variables as chart colors. The SVG fill uses var(--chart-primary) directly — no JavaScript color resolution needed. Toggle the theme or change palettes to see the chart react instantly via CSS.
{{ charts[0] }} {{ charts[1] }} {{ charts[2] }}

chart.options:
chart: {
  type: 'bar',
  height: 380,
  stacked: true,
},
colors: [
  'var(--chart-primary)',
  'var(--chart-secondary)',
  'var(--chart-tertiary)',
],
fill: {
  opacity: 0.85,
},
plotOptions: {
  bar: {
    borderRadius: 4,
    borderRadiusApplication: 'end',
    borderRadiusWhenStacked: 'last',
    horizontal: false,
    columnWidth: '55%',
  },
},
dataLabels: {
  enabled: false,
},
xaxis: {
  categories: ['Jan', 'Feb', 'Mar', 'Apr', 'May', 'Jun'],
},
legend: {
  position: 'top',
},
